  cpu-mode list [--json]       Enumerate the 4 named modes
                               (ultra-low-power / balanced /
                               sustained-burst / peak-inference).
  cpu-mode set <mode>          R221 (SDD-026 Z-4): switch CPU governor
                               to the named mode. Requires root; non-
                               root prints the actionable shell command.
  cpu-mode auto [--apply] [--aggressive] [--json]
                               R230 (SDD-026 Z-4): workload-aware mode
                               recommendation. Reads R215 inference
                               router + R219 GPU watt .prom files,
                               recommends a mode. Advisory by default;
                               --apply switches the governor.
  virt-info show [--json]      R255 (SDD-026 Z-19): virtualization +
                               PCIe lane + container-runtime snapshot.
                               Operator-named "pci lane splits and
                               whatever like virtualization".
  virt-info cpu [--json]       R255: CPU virt flags (vmx/svm + EPT/NPT).
  virt-info kvm [--json]       R255: KVM kernel module + /dev/kvm +
                               nested-virt state.
  virt-info iommu [--json]     R255: IOMMU sysfs + kernel cmdline
                               (intel_iommu=on / amd_iommu=on / ACS
                               override). Surfaces actionable advisory
                               when not enabled.
  virt-info pci [--json]       R255: per-device PCIe LnkSta width +
                               speed (GPUs, NVMe, NICs).
  virt-info runtimes [--json]  R255: docker / podman / containerd /
                               nerdctl / crun / runc detection.
  diagnose run [--severity S] [--limit N] [--all] [--json]
                               R266 (E6.M5): cross-axis diagnostic
                               synthesizer. Runs 8 sub-probes (health,
                               insights, power, bios, memory, virt,
                               services-advisor, install-paths),
                               aggregates findings ranked by severity
                               with Epic/Module tags. rc=1 when ≥1
                               critical finding. Distinct from the
                               legacy `doctor` verb (profile-aware
                               tooling check); this is the multi-axis
                               analysis layer named in operator's
                               "autohealth and doctor and analysis".
  diagnose probes [--json]     R266: list available sub-probes.
  operator-deps list|plan|apply [--confirm] [--confirm-curl-shell] [--json]
                               R284 (E7.M6): declarative dep-install
                               hook (apt / pip / npm / curl-shell).
                               Operator declares packages in
                               /etc/sovereign-os/operator-deps.toml;
                               apply requires --confirm AND for curl-
                               shell entries additionally requires
                               --confirm-curl-shell (defense-in-depth).
                               First cross-script consumer of the
                               R283 operator-overlay helper (SDD-030).
  mcp-aggregate manifest [--upstream-selfdef H:P] [--config P] [--json|--human]
  mcp-aggregate probe-upstream H:P [--timeout SECS] [--json]
                               R286 (E7.M5 / SDD-031): cross-repo
                               MCP-tool aggregator. Emits a unified
                               manifest of 31 sovereign-os read-only
                               MCP tools (every §1b-named axis) plus
                               optional --upstream-selfdef host:port
                               descriptor for selfdef MCP TCP (SD-R94).
                               Operator overlay knobs (extra_tools /
                               exclude_tools) honoured via SDD-030.
  research-loop status [--config P] [--json|--human]
  research-loop topics [--config P] [--json|--human]
                               R287 (E1.M19): hardware-exploit-to-the-
                               max research loop. status compares
                               operator-pinned baselines for the
                               AVX-512/Zen5 fast-path stack
                               (bitnet.cpp, Wasmtime, transformers,
                               vllm, trl, DFlash, etc) against
                               what's installed locally — rc=1 when
                               any tracked component drifts. topics
                               enumerates research questions anchored
                               to mandate Modules + SDDs. Operator
                               overlay (R283/SDD-030): replace track
                               + topics via /etc/sovereign-os/research-
                               loop.toml.
  next-steps next|packs|apply-pack [--severity S] [--limit N] [--json]
                               R282 (E5.M10): operator "assistant feel"
                               next-best-step synthesizer. Aggregates
                               every advisor surface's actions, ranks
                               by severity, emits a single prioritized
                               do-this-next list. `packs` lists curated
                               operator-packs (inference-burst,
                               headless-server, low-power, spec-
                               conformance, graceful-shutdown-rehearsal).
  wasm-aot status|compile-cmd <wasm>|advisory [--json]
                               R281 (E1.M17): Wasm-to-AVX-512 AOT
                               pipeline enforcer per master spec §20.
                               Checks wasmtime + Cranelift + the
                               WASMTIME_COMPARE_OPTIONS env knobs
                               (target-cpu=znver5 opt-level=3
                               relaxed-simd=true). compile-cmd emits
                               the canonical `taskset -c 0-11 wasmtime
                               compile --target x86_64 -O speed`
                               incantation.
  zmm-ternary status|perf-cmd|advisory [--json]
                               R280 (E1.M18): 1-bit/ternary ZMM
                               utilization probe per raw-dump §17.1+§20.
                               Checks AVX-512-F/VNNI/BF16 + bitnet.cpp/
                               T-MAC/transformers-bitnet toolchain
                               presence. perf-cmd emits the perf-stat
                               invocation operator runs to confirm
                               VPDPBUSD instructions actually retire
                               under live load.
  ram-advisor status|budget|advisory [--json]
                               R279 (E1.M16): 256 GB DDR5 RAM advisor
                               per master-spec §1.1+§3+§19. Composite
                               verdict over live MemTotal vs operator-
                               expected total + ZFS ARC ceiling (128
                               GiB clamp) + GGUF context budget +
                               non-AI headroom. Critical when live
                               total <10% below expected (DIMM fail)
                               OR ARC blew the ceiling.
  service-deps graph|drain|dot [--unit ...|--prefix P] [--json]
                               R277 (E2.M9): service-dependency graph
                               + topo-sorted drain order. Reads
                               systemd After/Wants/Requires/BindsTo
                               via `systemctl show` (falls back to
                               unit-file parse). drain emits leaves-
                               first stop order paste-able into a
